## ğŸ§­ Reporting Vulnerabilities

If you discover a security issue, please report it privately:

- Email: security@apzchain.org
- Do **not** open public issues for vulnerabilities.

We will respond within 72 hours and coordinate a responsible disclosure.

---

## ğŸ›¡ Scope

This policy applies to:

- Indexer logic and metric reporting
- Prometheus/Grafana setup
- CI/CD pipelines
- Docker configurations

---

## ğŸš« What to Avoid

- Hardcoded secrets or credentials
- Unvalidated external inputs
- Unrestricted access to metric endpoints
- Insecure Docker volumes or ports

---

## âœ… Best Practices

- Use environment variables for secrets
- Validate all inputs and RPC responses
- Limit Prometheus access to trusted sources
- Keep dependencies up-to-date

